{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1013,"text":"I want to talk about my investigations"},{"time":3575,"text":"into what technology means in our lives --"},{"time":8143,"text":"not just our immediate life,\nbut in the cosmic sense,"},{"time":11375,"text":"in the kind of long history of the world"},{"time":14541,"text":"and our place in the world."},{"time":17144,"text":"What is this stuff?"},{"time":19042,"text":"What is the significance?"},{"time":20526,"text":"And so, I want to kind of\ngo through my little story"},{"time":24458,"text":"of what I found out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25728,"text":"One of the first things\nI started to investigate"},{"time":28039,"text":"was the history of the name of technology."},{"time":30874,"text":"In the United States,\nthere is a State of the Union address"},{"time":33852,"text":"given by every president since 1790."},{"time":36771,"text":"And each one of those is kind of\nsumming up the most important things"},{"time":41833,"text":"for the United States at that time."},{"time":43563,"text":"If you search for the word \"technology,\"\nit was not used until 1952."},{"time":48873,"text":"So, technology was sort of absent\nfrom everybody's thinking until 1952,"},{"time":52995,"text":"which happened to be the year of my birth."},{"time":55070,"text":"And obviously, technology\nhad existed before then,"},{"time":58087,"text":"but we weren't aware of it."},{"time":59516,"text":"And so it was sort of an awakening\nof this force in our life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64138,"text":"I actually did research to find out\nthe first use of the word \"technology.\""},{"time":68375,"text":"It was in 1829,"},{"time":70375,"text":"and it was invented by a guy\nwho was starting a curriculum --"},{"time":73375,"text":"a course, bringing together all the kinds\nof arts and crafts, and industry --"},{"time":78025,"text":"and he called it \"Technology.\""},{"time":80010,"text":"And that's the very first use of the word."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82517,"text":"So what is this stuff"},{"time":84707,"text":"that we're all consumed by\nand bothered by?"},{"time":90018,"text":"Alan Kay calls it, \"Technology\nis anything that was invented"},{"time":92964,"text":"after you were born.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":94217,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95249,"text":"Which is sort of the idea we normally\nhave about what technology is:"},{"time":99708,"text":"it's all that new stuff."},{"time":101375,"text":"It's not roads, or penicillin,"},{"time":103602,"text":"or factory tires; it's the new stuff."},{"time":107389,"text":"My friend Danny Hillis\nsays kind of a similar one,"},{"time":109936,"text":"he says, \"Technology is anything\nthat doesn't work yet.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":112639,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113678,"text":"Which is, again,\na sense that it's all new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115742,"text":"But we know that it's just not new."},{"time":117474,"text":"It actually goes way back,"},{"time":118784,"text":"and what I want to suggest is,\nit goes a long way back."},{"time":122909,"text":"So, another way to think\nabout technology, what it means,"},{"time":125701,"text":"is to imagine a world without technology."},{"time":127749,"text":"If we were to eliminate every single bit\nof technology in the world today --"},{"time":131434,"text":"and I mean everything,\nfrom blades to scrapers to cloth --"},{"time":136375,"text":"we, as a species,\nwould not live very long."},{"time":139134,"text":"We would die by the billions,\nand very quickly:"},{"time":142135,"text":"the wolves would get us,\nwe would be defenseless,"},{"time":145464,"text":"we would be unable to grow\nenough food or find enough food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148681,"text":"Even the hunter-gatherers\nused some elementary tools."},{"time":152141,"text":"So, they had minimal technology,"},{"time":154497,"text":"but they had some technology."},{"time":156203,"text":"And if we study\nthose hunter-gatherer tribes"},{"time":159360,"text":"and the Neanderthal,\nwhich are very similar to early man,"},{"time":163036,"text":"we find out a very curious thing\nabout this world without technology,"},{"time":166347,"text":"and this is a kind of a curve\nof their average age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169200,"text":"There are no Neanderthal fossils\nthat are older than 40 years old"},{"time":173679,"text":"that we've ever found,"},{"time":175314,"text":"and the average age of most of these\nhunter-gatherer tribes is 20 to 30."},{"time":179568,"text":"There are very few young infants,\nbecause they die -- high mortality rate --"},{"time":184493,"text":"and there's very few old people."},{"time":186065,"text":"So the profile is sort of for your average\nSan Francisco neighborhood:"},{"time":189669,"text":"a lot of young people."},{"time":191098,"text":"And if you go there, you say,\n\"Hey, everybody's really healthy.\""},{"time":194186,"text":"Well, that's because they're all young."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196114,"text":"Same thing with the hunter-gatherer\ntribes and early man:"},{"time":198869,"text":"you didn't live beyond the age of 30."},{"time":200688,"text":"So it was a world without grandparents."},{"time":202689,"text":"And grandparents are very important,"},{"time":204746,"text":"because they are the transmitter\nof cultural evolution and information."},{"time":208409,"text":"Imagine a world where basically\neverybody was 20 to 30 years old."},{"time":211569,"text":"How much learning can you do?"},{"time":213237,"text":"You can't do very much\nlearning in your own life,"},{"time":215596,"text":"it's so short,"},{"time":216918,"text":"and there's nobody to pass on\nwhat you do learn."},{"time":219296,"text":"So that's one aspect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222267,"text":"It was a very short life."},{"time":223607,"text":"But at the same time, anthropologists know"},{"time":226423,"text":"that most hunter-gatherer\ntribes of the world,"},{"time":229027,"text":"with that very little technology,"},{"time":230713,"text":"actually did not spend a very long time\ngathering the food they needed:"},{"time":234223,"text":"three to six hours a day."},{"time":235830,"text":"Some anthropologists call that\nthe original affluent society,"},{"time":239875,"text":"because they had\nbankers' hours, basically."},{"time":242265,"text":"So it was possible to get enough food."},{"time":244923,"text":"But when the scarcity came,"},{"time":247448,"text":"when the highs and lows\nand the droughts came,"},{"time":249755,"text":"then people went into starvation."},{"time":252312,"text":"And that's why they didn't live very long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254384,"text":"So what technology brought,"},{"time":256823,"text":"through the very simple tools\nlike these stone tools here --"},{"time":261423,"text":"even something as small as this --"},{"time":263260,"text":"the early bands of humans were actually\nable to eliminate to extinction"},{"time":268689,"text":"about 250 megafauna animals\nin North America"},{"time":273805,"text":"when they first arrived 10,000 years ago."},{"time":276018,"text":"So, long before the industrial age,"},{"time":278683,"text":"we've been affecting\nthe planet on a global scale"},{"time":281375,"text":"with just a small amount of technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283530,"text":"The other thing that the early man\ninvented was fire."},{"time":286850,"text":"And fire was used to clear out, and again,"},{"time":288999,"text":"affected the ecology of grass\nand whole continents,"},{"time":292671,"text":"and was used in cooking."},{"time":295093,"text":"It enabled us to actually\neat all kinds of things."},{"time":297572,"text":"It was, in a certain sense,\nin a McLuhan sense,"},{"time":299850,"text":"an external stomach,"},{"time":301982,"text":"in the sense that it was cooking food\nthat we could not eat otherwise."},{"time":305501,"text":"And if we didn't have fire,\nwe actually could not live."},{"time":308269,"text":"Our bodies have adapted\nto these new diets."},{"time":311435,"text":"Our bodies have changed\nin the last 10,000 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314254,"text":"So, with that little bit of technology,"},{"time":317334,"text":"humans went from a small band\nof 10,000 or so --"},{"time":319634,"text":"the same number\nas Neanderthals everywhere --"},{"time":321807,"text":"and we suddenly exploded."},{"time":323069,"text":"With the invention of language\naround 50,000 years ago,"},{"time":325694,"text":"the number of humans exploded,"},{"time":327211,"text":"and very quickly became\nthe dominant species on the planet."},{"time":330359,"text":"And they migrated\ninto the rest of the world"},{"time":332825,"text":"at two kilometers per year"},{"time":334289,"text":"until, within several tens\nof thousands of years,"},{"time":337290,"text":"we occupied every single\nwatershed on the planet"},{"time":339589,"text":"and became the most dominant species,"},{"time":341431,"text":"with a very small amount of technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343818,"text":"And even at that time,\nwith the introduction of agriculture,"},{"time":346922,"text":"8,000, 10,000 years ago,"},{"time":348656,"text":"we started to see climate change."},{"time":350375,"text":"So climate change is not a new thing;\nwhat's new is just the degree of it."},{"time":353983,"text":"Even during the agricultural age,\nthere was climate change."},{"time":357082,"text":"So already, small amounts of technology\nwere transforming the world."},{"time":360842,"text":"And what this means, and where I'm going,"},{"time":363527,"text":"is that technology has become\nthe most powerful force in the world."},{"time":367375,"text":"All the things we see today\nthat are changing our lives,"},{"time":370326,"text":"we can always trace back"},{"time":371537,"text":"to the introduction\nof some new technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373626,"text":"So it's a force,"},{"time":374955,"text":"that is the most powerful force\nthat has been unleashed on this planet,"},{"time":379050,"text":"and in such a degree,"},{"time":380883,"text":"that I think it's become who we are."},{"time":387128,"text":"In fact, our humanity and everything\nthat we think about ourselves,"},{"time":390407,"text":"is something we've invented."},{"time":391899,"text":"So we've invented ourselves."},{"time":393330,"text":"Of all the animals\nthat we've domesticated,"},{"time":395472,"text":"the most important animal has been us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398833,"text":"So humanity is our greatest invention,"},{"time":402375,"text":"but of course, we're not done yet."},{"time":404375,"text":"We're still inventing,"},{"time":405561,"text":"and this is what technology\nis allowing us to do;"},{"time":407923,"text":"it's continually to reinvent ourselves."},{"time":409983,"text":"It's a very, very strong force."},{"time":412430,"text":"I call this entire thing --\nus humans as our technology,"},{"time":415589,"text":"everything that we've made,\ngadgets in our lives --"},{"time":418375,"text":"we call that the technium."},{"time":419662,"text":"That's this world."},{"time":420846,"text":"My working definition of technology is:"},{"time":422775,"text":"anything useful that a human mind makes."},{"time":425172,"text":"It's not just hammers\nand gadgets, like laptops."},{"time":427854,"text":"But it's also law."},{"time":429299,"text":"And, of course, cities are ways\nto make things more useful to us."},{"time":434466,"text":"While this is something\nthat comes from our mind,"},{"time":436955,"text":"it also has its roots\ndeeply into the cosmos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441272,"text":"It goes back."},{"time":442459,"text":"The origins and roots of technology\ngo back to the Big Bang,"},{"time":445346,"text":"in this way, in that they are part\nof this self-organizing thread"},{"time":449858,"text":"that starts at the Big Bang\nand goes through galaxies and stars,"},{"time":454437,"text":"into life, into us."},{"time":456019,"text":"And the three major phases\nof the early universe"},{"time":458671,"text":"was energy, when the dominant\nforce was energy;"},{"time":460917,"text":"then the dominant force,\nas it cooled, became matter;"},{"time":463981,"text":"and then, with the invention\nof life four billion years ago,"},{"time":467375,"text":"the dominant force in our neighborhood\nbecame information."},{"time":470185,"text":"That's what life is:"},{"time":471393,"text":"an information process\nthat was restructuring"},{"time":473577,"text":"and making new order."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474823,"text":"So, energy and matter,\nEinstein showed were equivalent,"},{"time":478464,"text":"and now new sciences of quantum computing\nshow that entropy and information"},{"time":484108,"text":"and matter and energy"},{"time":485582,"text":"are all interrelated."},{"time":486770,"text":"So it's one long continuum."},{"time":489204,"text":"You put energy\ninto the right kind of system,"},{"time":492423,"text":"and out comes wasted heat, entropy,"},{"time":495521,"text":"and extropy, which is order."},{"time":498375,"text":"It's the increased order."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499729,"text":"Where does this order come from?"},{"time":501306,"text":"Its roots go way back."},{"time":502601,"text":"We actually don't know."},{"time":503958,"text":"But we do know"},{"time":505194,"text":"that the self-organization trend\nthroughout the universe is long,"},{"time":509513,"text":"and it began with things like galaxies;"},{"time":511760,"text":"they maintained their order\nfor billions of years."},{"time":514278,"text":"Stars are basically\nnuclear fission machines"},{"time":518152,"text":"that self-organize and self-sustain\nthemselves for billions of years:"},{"time":521475,"text":"order against the extropy of the world."},{"time":523630,"text":"And flowers and plants\nare the same thing, extended,"},{"time":528564,"text":"and technology is basically\nan extension of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534223,"text":"One trend that we notice\nin all those things"},{"time":537225,"text":"is that the amount of energy\nper gram per second"},{"time":539821,"text":"that flows through this"},{"time":541128,"text":"is actually increasing."},{"time":542443,"text":"The amount of energy is increasing\nthrough this little sequence."},{"time":547046,"text":"And the amount of energy per gram\nper second that flows through life"},{"time":551047,"text":"is actually greater than a star --"},{"time":553048,"text":"because of the star's long lifespan,"},{"time":556375,"text":"the energy density in life\nis actually higher than a star."},{"time":559588,"text":"And the energy density\nthat we see in the greatest amount"},{"time":562471,"text":"anywhere in the universe"},{"time":563701,"text":"is actually in a PC chip."},{"time":565058,"text":"There is more energy flowing\nthrough, per gram per second,"},{"time":568232,"text":"than anything that we have\nany other experience with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571374,"text":"And so, what I would suggest"},{"time":573027,"text":"is that if you want to see\nwhere technology is going,"},{"time":575992,"text":"we continue that trajectory,"},{"time":577648,"text":"and we say, \"Well, it's going\nto become more energy-dense,"},{"time":580525,"text":"that's where it's going.\""},{"time":581766,"text":"And so what I've done is,\nI've taken the same kinds of things"},{"time":584758,"text":"and looked at other aspects\nof evolutionary life and say,"},{"time":588048,"text":"\"What are the general trends\nin evolutionary life?\""},{"time":590678,"text":"And there are things moving\ntowards greater complexity,"},{"time":593424,"text":"moving towards greater diversity,\nmoving towards greater specialization,"},{"time":597375,"text":"sentience, ubiquity,\nand most important, evolvability."},{"time":601641,"text":"Those very same things\nare also present in technology."},{"time":605188,"text":"That's where technology is going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607061,"text":"In fact, technology\nis accelerating all the aspects of life."},{"time":612375,"text":"And we can see that happening;"},{"time":613897,"text":"just as there's diversity in life,\nthere's more diversity in things we make."},{"time":618072,"text":"Things in life start off\nbeing general cells,"},{"time":620246,"text":"and they become specialized:"},{"time":621651,"text":"you have tissue cells,\nmuscle, brain cells."},{"time":623812,"text":"The same thing happens\nwith, say, a hammer,"},{"time":625866,"text":"which is general at first\nand becomes more specific."},{"time":628375,"text":"So I would like to say\nthat while there are six kingdoms of life,"},{"time":631495,"text":"we can think of technology\nbasically as a seventh kingdom of life."},{"time":635100,"text":"It's a branching off from the human form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637455,"text":"But technology has its own agenda,\nlike anything, like life itself."},{"time":641375,"text":"For instance, right now,\nthree-quarters of the energy that we use"},{"time":644541,"text":"is actually used to feed\nthe technium itself."},{"time":646697,"text":"In transportation, it's not to move us;"},{"time":648613,"text":"it's to move the stuff we make or buy."},{"time":650506,"text":"I use the word \"want.\" Technology wants."},{"time":652507,"text":"This is a robot that wants to plug\nitself in to get more power."},{"time":655533,"text":"Your cat wants more food."},{"time":658136,"text":"A bacterium, which has\nno consciousness at all,"},{"time":660723,"text":"wants to move towards light."},{"time":662375,"text":"It has an urge,\nand technology has an urge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665087,"text":"At the same time,\nit wants to give us things,"},{"time":667255,"text":"and what it gives us\nis basically progress."},{"time":669833,"text":"You can take all kinds of curves,\nand they're all pointing up."},{"time":672929,"text":"There's really no dispute about progress,"},{"time":675375,"text":"if we discount the cost of that."},{"time":678375,"text":"And that's the thing\nthat bothers most people,"},{"time":680590,"text":"is that progress is really real,\nbut we wonder and question:"},{"time":684478,"text":"What are the environmental costs of it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686375,"text":"I did a survey of the number\nof species of artifacts in my house,"},{"time":690226,"text":"and there's 6,000."},{"time":691408,"text":"Other people have come up with 10,000."},{"time":693501,"text":"When King Henry of England died,"},{"time":695965,"text":"he had 18,000 things in his house,"},{"time":698043,"text":"but that was the entire\nwealth of England, so ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701544,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702778,"text":"And with that entire wealth of England,"},{"time":705308,"text":"King Henry could not buy any antibiotics,"},{"time":708258,"text":"he could not buy refrigeration,"},{"time":709832,"text":"he could not buy\na trip of a thousand miles,"},{"time":711989,"text":"whereas this rickshaw wallah in India\ncould save up and buy antibiotics"},{"time":716477,"text":"and he could buy refrigeration."},{"time":718244,"text":"He could buy things that King Henry,\nin all his wealth, could never buy."},{"time":721739,"text":"That's what progress is about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723430,"text":"So, technology is selfish;\ntechnology is generous."},{"time":726375,"text":"That conflict, that tension,\nwill be with us forever:"},{"time":729595,"text":"sometimes it wants to do\nwhat it wants to do,"},{"time":731817,"text":"and sometimes it's going\nto do things for us."},{"time":733961,"text":"We have confusion\nabout what we should think"},{"time":736052,"text":"about a new technology."},{"time":737375,"text":"Right now the default position\nwhen a new technology comes along,"},{"time":741229,"text":"is people talk about\nthe precautionary principle,"},{"time":743578,"text":"which is very common in Europe,"},{"time":745488,"text":"which says, basically, \"Don't do anything."},{"time":747559,"text":"When you meet a new technology, stop,"},{"time":750197,"text":"until it can be proven\nthat it does no harm.\""},{"time":752750,"text":"I think that really leads nowhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755019,"text":"But a better way is\nwhat I call the proactionary principle,"},{"time":758044,"text":"which is, you engage with technology."},{"time":760474,"text":"You try it out."},{"time":761876,"text":"You obviously do what the precautionary\nprinciple suggests,"},{"time":766116,"text":"you try to anticipate it,"},{"time":767385,"text":"but after anticipating it,"},{"time":768836,"text":"you constantly asses it,"},{"time":770375,"text":"not just once, but eternally."},{"time":771962,"text":"And when it diverts from what you want,"},{"time":775163,"text":"we prioritize risk,\nwe evaluate not just the new stuff,"},{"time":778348,"text":"but the old stuff."},{"time":779531,"text":"We fix it; but most importantly,"},{"time":781425,"text":"we relocate it."},{"time":782606,"text":"And what I mean by that is,"},{"time":784454,"text":"we find a new job for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786186,"text":"Nuclear energy, fission,\nis a really bad idea for bombs."},{"time":790220,"text":"But it may be a pretty good idea\nrelocated into sustainable nuclear energy"},{"time":795639,"text":"for electricity, instead of burning coal."},{"time":797981,"text":"When we have a bad idea,"},{"time":799720,"text":"the response to a bad idea"},{"time":801308,"text":"is not no ideas,\nit's not to stop thinking."},{"time":804652,"text":"The response to a bad idea --"},{"time":806829,"text":"like, say, a tungsten lightbulb --"},{"time":808981,"text":"is a better idea."},{"time":811713,"text":"So, better ideas\nis really always the response"},{"time":815217,"text":"to technology we don't like;"},{"time":816606,"text":"it's basically better technology."},{"time":819199,"text":"And actually, in a certain sense,\ntechnology is a kind of a method"},{"time":823043,"text":"for generating better ideas,"},{"time":824622,"text":"if you can think about it that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826375,"text":"So, maybe spraying DDT\non crops is a really bad idea."},{"time":829494,"text":"But DDT sprayed on local homes --"},{"time":832375,"text":"there's nothing better\nto eliminate malaria,"},{"time":835375,"text":"besides insect DDT-impregnated\nmosquito nets."},{"time":839137,"text":"But that's a really good idea;\nthat's a good job for technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842492,"text":"So our job as humans\nis to parent our mind children,"},{"time":846375,"text":"to find them good friends,"},{"time":847843,"text":"to find them a good job."},{"time":849259,"text":"And so, every technology\nis sort of a creative force"},{"time":852091,"text":"looking for the right job."},{"time":854135,"text":"That's actually my son, right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856250,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":857597,"text":"There are no bad technologies,"},{"time":860113,"text":"just as there are no bad children."},{"time":861833,"text":"We don't say children are neutral;\nchildren are positive."},{"time":864739,"text":"We just have to find them the right place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867090,"text":"And so, what technology gives us\nover the long term --"},{"time":871068,"text":"over this sort of extended evolution\nfrom the beginning of time,"},{"time":874733,"text":"through the invention\nof the plants and animals,"},{"time":878375,"text":"and the evolution of life,\nthe evolution of brains --"},{"time":881375,"text":"what that is constantly giving us\nis increasing differences:"},{"time":885310,"text":"It's increasing diversity,\nit's increasing options,"},{"time":887789,"text":"it's increasing choices, opportunities,\npossibilities and freedoms."},{"time":891791,"text":"That's what we get\nfrom technology all the time."},{"time":894739,"text":"That's why people leave villages\nand go into cities --"},{"time":897579,"text":"because they are always gravitating\ntowards increased choices"},{"time":901252,"text":"and possibilities."},{"time":902513,"text":"And we are aware of the price;"},{"time":905166,"text":"we pay a price for that,\nbut we're aware of it,"},{"time":907429,"text":"and generally, we will pay the price\nfor increased freedoms,"},{"time":910408,"text":"choices and opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912305,"text":"Even technology wants clean water."},{"time":915037,"text":"Is technology diametrically\nopposed to nature?"},{"time":919242,"text":"Because technology\nis an extension of life,"},{"time":922124,"text":"it's in parallel and aligned\nwith the same things"},{"time":924991,"text":"that life wants."},{"time":926874,"text":"So that I think technology loves biology,"},{"time":929073,"text":"if we allow it to."},{"time":931231,"text":"Great movement\nstarting billions of years ago"},{"time":935375,"text":"is moving through us\nand it continues to go,"},{"time":937703,"text":"and our choice, so to speak,\nin technology,"},{"time":941140,"text":"is really to align ourselves\nwith this force"},{"time":943235,"text":"much greater than ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944643,"text":"So, technology is more\nthan just the stuff in your pocket;"},{"time":947475,"text":"it's more than just gadgets,"},{"time":948890,"text":"it's more than just things\nthat people invent."},{"time":951379,"text":"It's actually part of a very long\nstory -- a great story --"},{"time":954790,"text":"that began billions of years ago."},{"time":956447,"text":"It's moving through us,\nthis self-organization,"},{"time":958778,"text":"and we're extending and accelerating it,"},{"time":960779,"text":"and we can be part of it by aligning\nthe technology that we make with it."},{"time":964567,"text":"And I really appreciate\nyour attention today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967429,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968612,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}